               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Dīvān by Maghribī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1367-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of poetic compositions in varied forms and genres (ghazal and rubāʿī) by the Sufi and poet, Shaykh Muḥammad Shīrīn ibn ʿIzz al-Dīn Yūsuf Nāʾinī Iṣfahānī Tabrīzī takhalluṣ Maghribī (d. 809/1406-7), a close friend of the Timurid Prince Sulṭān Mīrān Shāh (d. 810/1408) and later rival of the court poet Shaykh Kamāl al-Dīn Khujandī Tabrīzī takhalluṣ Kamāl (d. 803/1400).</p>
                        <p>Partially dated colophon (f. 77): completed by Javāhir Mal (written as unconnected initials) at the request (ḥasb al-farmūdah) of Miyān ʿAbd al-Raḥmān, Muḥarram 1074/August 1663.</p>
                        <p>Rough nastaʿlīq.</p>
                        <p>Annotations in margins and vacant spaces by multiple later hands.</p>
                        <p>Lacking binding. Folios unbound; water and oil stains, foxing, smudging, creasing, wormholes, cropped, later repairs.</p>
                        <p>Condition poor.</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656345.0x000001 viaf_12221201">Maghribī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_12221201">مغربى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20622">Dīvān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20622">دیوان</title>
                  </msItem>
